          The Murg Valley Railway Karlsruhe - Freudenstadt
          ================================================

From Karlsruhe start hourly trains on the route to the Murgtal, the
river valley of the Murg in the Black Forrest. Until Rastatt the trains
run on the Rhine River Valley Line, in Rastatt begins the actual
Murgtalbahn. Because only the Rhine River Valley Line is electrified,
Diesel or steam locos must be used (in normal traffic of course
Diesel). The last part of the route between Baiersbronn and
Freudenstadt is fairly steep (1 in 37), therefore only specially
suited locos are accepted. In TD3 this is cared for by setting the
switch Loco x 2 for Diesel and Loco x 3 for steam. Diesels should not
have more than 5 coaches,steam not more than 4.

I am sorry, that for the making of the route I only had the time
table, all other items I took out of the map and out of own experience
on the route. The TD3 route is not quite ready jet, it needs some more
scenery etc. But it shows quite well some of the special features of
TD3 and it still can be run with TD2.

